{
  "name": "VIOLET CITY",
  "_note": "Phase 7 build (docs/violet-city-design.md) — a lived-in highland town that winds. Entered from the NORTH (walk south down Route 31). The ACADEMY (ancient stone, enterable) is the elevated centerpiece at the heart; the SQUARE + founding STATUE sit before it, with the Concord kiosk/billboard/rep re-homed into that same square (the old way and the shortcut side by side). Center/Mart/Gym sit organically off winding paths; 3 flavor houses at varied angles; a LOOKOUT over the valley at the southwest edge. PLACEHOLDER ART (HGSS pass is Phase 7 polish). Anchors fixed for the spine/tests: north exit (9,0), gym door (9,12), spawns. Existing verbs only; one-time lines flag-gated.",
